{{Infobox Website |name = XBIZ |logo = |screenshot = |caption = |url = [http://xbiz.com XBIZ.com] |commercial = Yes |type = [[News website]] |language = [[English language|English]] |registration = No |owner = Adnet Media |author = Adnet Media |launch date = 1998 |current status = |revenue = |slogan = The Industry Source }} '''XBIZ (XBiz)''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Trade magazine|trade website]] covering the [[adult entertainment]] industry, which launched in 1998. The website and its writers are frequently quoted in mainstream newspaper articles about the industry.<ref>{{cite news |author=Jonathan Curiel |title=NEWSPAPERS TURN TO SEX AND CELEBS |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2007/03/04/ING44OD5701.DTL |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=[[March 4]] [[2007]] |accessdate=2008-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Dana Bartholomew |title=The Valley Exposed: The Future of Porn |url=http://www.dailynews.com/news/ci_6093913 |work=[[Los Angeles Daily News]] |date=[[June 8]] [[2007]] |accessdate=2008-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Dominic Rushe |title=Outsourced porn gives more bang for its buck |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,2095-2281135,00.html |work=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=[[July 23]] [[2006]] |accessdate=2008-03-18}}</ref> The website is also cited extensively as a reference on [[Wikipedia]]. Its main competitor is [[Adult Video News]] (AVN).
XBIZ was launched in 1998 by Adnet Media. XBIZ provides the adult industry informational and collaboration resources designed to help both new and experienced adult business operators succeed. <ref name=about>[http://www.xbiz.com/about/ About XBIZ]. Retrieved on [[2008-03-18]].</ref>
Informational resources include: *industry news *feature articles *industry directory *message boards *blogs *events calendar *business services.<ref name=about />
==XBIZ Awards== {{main|XBIZ Award}} The annual XBIZ Awards are [[List of movie awards|movie awards]] sponsored and presented by ''XBIZ'' to honor exceptional performance in various aspects of the creation and marketing of [[adult entertainment]]. The awards coincide with the ''XBIZ Conference'' held in [[Woodland Hills, California]].{{Fact|date=January 2009}}
