{{refimprove|date=June 2006}}
'''Porn groove''' (or '''porno groove''') is a term used to describe the music [[soundtrack]] to [[Pornographic movie|pornographic films]], or a [[Music genre|genre]] of music that imitates such music. The [[electric guitar]] with [[wah-wah pedal]] is the most common instrument associated with porn groove, and synonymous with the genre. Simple, often [[minimalist music|minimalistic]]-sounding drums, with the [[rim knock]] sound being commonly associated with porn groove. In some movies such as the popular and influential ''[[Deep Throat (film)|Deep Throat]]'', the film is cut with the music in mind, making the 'thrust' in the scenes 'flow' with the music.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fusedmagazine.com/Past_Issues/Issue_22/Deep_Throat.aspx |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080105051415/http://www.fusedmagazine.com/Past_Issues/Issue_22/Deep_Throat.aspx |archivedate=2008-01-01 |title=Archive - ''Deep Throat'' |work=[[Fused Magazine]] |quote=Gerard Damiano edited the film to its music, so the actions would match and the beat would match…like up and down strokes on the old shaft…it was pretty clever.}}</ref> Porn groove is often thought of as quite [[wikt:tacky|tacky]] music.
In the [[ID3]] genre notation for [[MP3]] music files, "Porn Groove" is a predefined option.
