'''Right to pornography''' refers to the [[Rights|right]] of an individual to produce, distribute and watch [[pornography]]. The concept is established since as early as 1960s. ''Daily Record'' reported in April 8, 1969 that the [[Supreme Court of the United States]] declared that every citizen has "constitutional right to keep and enjoy pornographic material in his home."<ref>[http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=hV4KAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5ksDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5171,404693&dq=right-to-pornography Court Proclaims Citizen's Right To Pornography] ''Daily Record''</ref>
