Dogma is incorporated as OM Production, Inc. (株式会社オムプロダクション) with Muneyuki Mikami (三上宗之) as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. The company has its offices and studios in [[Tokyo]]'s [[Roppongi]] district.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dogma.co.jp/modules/tinyd2/index.php?id=21|title=Company Information|publisher=[http://www.dogma.co.jp/ www.dogma.co.jp]|accessdate=2009-02-26|language=Japanese}}</ref>
==Series and labels== Dogma specializes in extreme videos depicting various fetish genres including [[anal sex]], [[Bondage (BDSM)|bondage]], [[Sadomasochism|S&M]], forced [[fellatio]] and vomiting, enemas, [[Urolagnia|watersports]] and [[Coprophilia|scat]]. One of Dogma's longest running series is the S&M "M-Drug" (Mドラッグ) series directed by [[Tohjiro]] and begun in September 2005 with [[Mayura Hoshitsuki]]. Another Tohjiro series is "Confinement Chair Trance" (拘束椅子トランス) which started up in November 2002. Tohjiro is also the director of the "Innocent Desire" (青い性欲) lolita-genre series which premiered in March 2001 when Dogma was still part of SOD. Another extensive series is the [[Futanari|"Hermaphrodite"]] (ふたなり) set of videos directed by Hitoshi Nimura.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dogma.co.jp/modules/webshop/search_d.php?dat=18&pd=download|title=Series|publisher=[http://www.dogma.co.jp/ www.dogma.co.jp]|accessdate=2009-02-25}}</ref><ref name="javnews">{{cite web |url=http://www.superjav.com/blog/?p=89|title=JAV News - Popular Series and Actors from Dogma Studio|accessdate=2008-09-14|publisher=[http://www.superjav.com/ JAV News]|month=August |year=2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jans-web.com/?p=series&sid=86|title=Film Series: Dogma - Confinement Chair Trance 拘束椅子トランス|accessdate=2009-03-03|publisher=[http://www.jans-web.com/ Urabon Navigator]}}</ref>
Most Dogma videos have been released under the Dogma label but [[Tohjiro]] instituted a separate hardcore S&M themed label, CORE SM, in December 2005 with its first release being ''Maki Tomoda - Bound Masochistic Slave''. Another label, Shyness, was started in November 2007 to continue the "Innocent Desire" lolita-genre series and a third label, Dogma Out, was used in 2005 and 2006 mostly by director Baba the Babee. The CORE label uses the production code series COT-xxx, Shyness uses DDH-xxx, and Dogma Out uses ODD-xxx.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dogma.co.jp/modules/webshop/search_d.php?dat=4&pd=download|title=Label|publisher=[http://www.dogma.co.jp/ www.dogma.co.jp]|accessdate=2009-02-25}}</ref>
