==D-1 Climax Awards== Dogma sponsored the [[Japanese Adult Video Awards#Dogma D-1 Climax Awards (2005-2007)|D-1 Climax]] (D-1 クライマックス) awards, which ran from 2005 to 2007, as a competition for directors. Several prominent directors from Dogma and other companies were invited to make videos under the Dogma label and sales during a set period plus voting by judges were used to determine the winners of the contest. Director and founder [[Tohjiro]] won the award in 2005 and 2006 but Hitoshi Nimura took the prize in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://allabout.co.jp/entertainment/adultvideo/closeup/CU20061224A/index3.htm| title=最エロな監督と女優が決定！Ｄ１クライマックス授賞式 (Porn Actresses & Best Director - D-1 Climax Ceremony)|accessdate=2008-11-20|publisher=[http://allabout.co.jp/ All About]|date=December 24, 2006|last=Otsubo|first=Kemuta|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dogma.co.jp/htmls/d-1/products/results.html|title=D-1 Climax Director's 1 Results|publisher=[http://www.dogma.co.jp/ www.dogma.co.jp]|accessdate=2008-11-20|language=Japanese}}</ref>
==AV GrandPrix== Dogma had not participated in the [[AV Open]] contests in 2006 and 2007 but with the ending of the D-1 Climax Awards, Dogma did enter a video in the Maniac Stage of the 2008 [[AV GrandPrix]], a compilation from [[Tohjiro]]'s M-Drug series ''Best of M Drug - Female Meat Toilet'' (Mドラッグ・スペシャル 女体肉便器ベスト) [AVGL-019].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dmm.co.jp/avgp/sp/mania_list.html|title=AV Grand Prix 2008 Mania Stage|publisher=[http://www.dmm.co.jp/ www.dmm.co.jp]|accessdate=2008-10-05|language=Japanese}}</ref> For the 2009 AV GrandPrix competition, the Dogma entry was another Tohjiro production, ''Vomit Enema Ecstasy X'' (ゲロ浣腸エクスタシー Ｘ) [AVGL-130] starring [[Mayura Hoshitsuki]] and Yuka Oosawa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.av-gp.com/works/avgl130/bottom.html|title=Dogma Entry|publisher=[http://www.av-gp.com/ www.av-gp.com]|accessdate=2009-03-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> Tohjiro made some waves by declaring all-out war by the small "indie" producer Dogma to defeat last year's champion, top studio [[S1 No. 1 Style]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dogma.co.jp/htmls/AVGP2009/index.html|title=AVGP 2009|publisher=[http://www.dogma.co.jp/ www.dogma.co.jp]|accessdate=2009-03-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> Although S1 did take the GrandPrix top prize and several others, Tohjiro made good on part of his boast - the Dogma video won the Digital Sales Award and the 2 million yen (about $20,000) prize money.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.av-gp.com/news/avgp_result/bottom.html|title=AVGP 2009 Result announcement|publisher=[http://www.av-gp.com/ www.av-gp.com]|accessdate=2009-03-02|language=Japanese}}</ref>
