{{Male adult bio| | image = [[Image:Replace this image male.svg]] | caption = | birth = 1958 | location = [[Kanagawa Prefecture]], [[Japan]] | birthname = | death = | height = | weight = | eye color = | hair color = | ethnicity = [[Japanese people|Japanese]] | alias = | number of films = | homepage = | imdb = | iafd = | afdb = }}
{{nihongo|'''Ganari Takahashi'''|高橋がなり|Takahashi Ganari}} is an entrepreneur in the field of Japanese [[adult video]] (AV). He founded [[Soft On Demand]] (SOD), one of the largest porn conglomerates in Japan.
==Life and career== Takahashi, whose real name is Masaya Takahashi (高橋 雅也), was born in [[Kanagawa Prefecture]], [[Japan]] in 1958. After graduating from high school he went to work as a driver for the Sagawa Express Co. where he made himself into the best driver in the company. In 1981 he joined the TV production company IVS where he worked for Terry Itoh ([[:ja:テリー伊藤]]) directing shows such as ''Tensai Takeshi no Genki ga deru TV'' (Genius Takeshi’s Exhilarating TV Show). He also later worked at a Chinese restaurant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elevenarts.net/Feature/Titles/OhMyZombie/OhMyZombieMermaid.pdf|title=Oh! My Zombie Mermaid|publisher=[http://www.elevenarts.net/ www.elevenarts.net]|accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref><ref name="xonge">{{cite web|url=http://xonge.com/?tag=ganari-takahashi|title=Ganari Takahashi|publisher=[http://xonge.com/ XONGE]|language=Chinese|accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref>
===SOD=== Takahashi used 10 million Yen (about $100,000) borrowed from Itoh to invest in two companies, one in golf-related goods and the other in the apparel business, but both failed. About that time, an AV company with about 10 employees was on the edge of bankruptcy and Takahashi with help from Itoh was able to use the company as the basis for the foundation of [[Soft On Demand]] (SOD) in 1995.<ref name="xonge"/> Takahashi was able to grow SOD into a major company, from sales of 300 million yen (about $3 million) in 1996 to 6 billion yen (about $60 million) by 2001 and to 9 billion yen (about $90 million) in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://softondemand.jp/corporate/company/data.html|title=SOD Company Data|publisher=[http://softondemand.jp/ SOD]|accessdate=2008-12-09|language=Japanese}}</ref> In 2003 the company had a staff of 180 and was generating profits of 1.5 billion yen (about $15 million) on sales from 1000 titles a year. Takahashi's plan was to increase market share and to absorb or eliminate competition from the hundreds of other AV manufacturers by producing high quality products at lower prices ("We want to spend money making good movies that we can sell cheaply") and by removing some of the stigma attached to adult products ("I want people to know that there's nothing dirty about adult videos").<ref name="japaninc">{{cite web|url=http://www.japaninc.com/article.php?articleID=1188|title=The Ray Kroc of Adult Video|publisher=[http://www.japaninc.com/ Japan Inc]|accessdate=2009-04-01|last=McNeill|first=David|date=September 2003}}</ref><ref name="offbeat">{{cite news|title=Offbeat erotica pumps porno-maker into big time|last=Connell|first=Ryann|url=http://mdn.mainichi-msn.co.jp/waiwai/archive/news/2001/06/20010605p2g00m0dm999000c.html|work=[[Mainichi Shimbun]]|date=June 5, 2001|accessdate=2007-03-06}} This source is no longer available but a copy of the article can be accessed at http://cid-88684d2bf683ba51.skydrive.live.com/self.aspx/mainichi/moto/2001/2001.06/Offbeat%20erotica%20pumps%20porno-maker%20into%20big%20time.pdf</ref>
In addition, Takahashi, who has been described as "strong-willed"<ref name="works">{{cite web|url=http://www.jmate.com/reviews/article_123.html|title=The Collection of Works ~ Ganari Takahashi|publisher=[http://www.jmate.com/ JMate]|accessdate=2009-04-01}}</ref> and "out-spoken",<ref name="animaxis">{{cite web|url=http://www.animaxis.com/en/zine/newsletter/view.asp?id=N001249|title=Major Adult Film Company to Produce Children's Anime |publisher=[http://www.animaxis.com/en/ Animaxis.com]|accessdate=2009-04-01}}</ref> made SOD into one of the most creative, innovative and outrageous AV companies in Japan. One of his stunts involved using a crane to raise couples on a trasparent platform 20 meters into the air where they engaged in sex which climaxed in a bungee jump from the platform. Another large-scale production, ''All Naked Airborne F**k'', filmed from a helicopter, proved to be one of his rare failures with the public but Takahashi felt that the video "showed our customers that we weren't afraid to spend the dough on making a good flick".<ref name="xonge"/><ref name="works"/><ref name="offbeat"/>
===Agriculture=== Takahashi retired from SOD at the end of fiscal year 2005 (March)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.livedoor.jp/sod/|title=高橋がなりブログ 虎の声 - SOD (Voice of the Tigers blog Takahashi - SOD)|publisher=[http://blog.livedoor.jp Livedoor Blogs]|accessdate=2009-04-02}}</ref><ref name="xonge"/> and used the 1 billion yen (about $10 million) "[[golden handshake]]" he received to purchase a farm in suburban Tokyo which would provide fresh produce to be served at his nearby restaurant. He traveled to farms all over Japan to learn the business and planned to bring his innovative style to farming as well - with a little pushing: "Everybody who works for me is an idiot, who keeps saying how things can't be done instead of using their heads and trying to work out the ways things can be done".<ref>{{cite news |first=Ryann|last=Connell|title=Japan's king of porn gets his hands dirty once again -- on the farm|url=http://mdn.mainichi.jp/culture/waiwai/archive/news/2007/02/20070226p2g00m0dm004000c.html|publisher=[[February 26]], [[2007]]|date= |accessdate=2007-03-06}} The original source is no longer available but a copy of the article can be accessed at http://www.amust4sex.com/adultnews/archives/2007/02.html</ref>
Takahashi started his new company "National Farm" (国立ファーム) in 2006 with the goal of trying to improve farm products saying that years of government subsidies had discouraged farmers - "The farmers are not rewarded for producing better agricultural products". Takahashi's solution was to support new farming techniques and to encourage farmers by opening a series of restaurants buying fresh vegetable produce directly from farmers. A second restaurant was opened in the [[Roppongi]] district of Tokyo in November 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insightnow.jp/article/51|title=百姓になった高橋がなりの『農家の台所』 (Takahashi and the farmer's kitchen)|publisher=[http://www.insightnow.jp/ Insight Now]|date=April 8, 2007|accessdate=2009-04-01|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insightnow.jp/article/3055|title=高橋がなり・国立ファームの今後の事業戦略 (Business Strategy and the Future of Takahashi's National Farm)|publisher=[http://www.insightnow.jp/ Insight Now]|date=March 23, 2009|accessdate=2009-04-01|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iza.ne.jp/news/newsarticle/business/manufacturer/198790|title=農家直送の新鮮野菜提供 国立ファーム２号店オープン (National Farm Offering Vegetables Direct from Farm Store Opening 2)|publisher=[http://www.iza.ne.jp/news/ www.iza.ne.jp/news]|date=November 25, 2008|accessdate=2009-04-02|language=Japanese}}</ref>
===Other activities=== After leaving SOD, Takahashi did make one more foray into the AV business for the 2007 [[AV Open]] contest. His entry, ''Making AV Debut Without Being Nude'' (絶対にAVには出ません！というグラビアアイドルを「君なら裸にならないAV女優になれる」と口説いてAVに出てもらいました) [OPEN-0719] starring Mao Hirai, was made under the label of his first restaurant "Kunitachi Farm".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dmm.co.jp/mono/dvd/avopen/avopen02.html|title=AV Open Entries|publisher=[http://www.dmm.co.jp/ www.dmm.co.jp]|accessdate=2008-10-02|language=Japanese}}</ref> The video finished in 5th place in the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dmm.co.jp/mono/dvd/avopen/avopen02_result.html|title=2nd AV Open Results|publisher=[http://www.dmm.co.jp/ www.dmm.co.jp]|accessdate=2008-10-02|language=Japanese}}</ref>
Takahashi is married and has children.<ref name="japaninc"/> When SOD announced plans in 2004 to produce an adaptation of the [[Shougakukan]] [[Big Comic Original]] [[manga]] series "Ajisai no Uta" (Song of Hydrangea) as an [[original video animation]] (OAV), Takahashi said he started the project because he and his wife both enjoyed the manga and he wanted to make something his 6-year old son could enjoy.<ref name="animaxis"/>
