==Campakex== Campakex was an indie rock band started by Matsushima Cross and Innjean Koga in 2004.<ref name="spysee"/> The group released the CD ''Level of Campakex'' through Komatsu Records on June 9, 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barks.jp/cdreview/?id=2000408845|title=Level of Campakex|publisher=[http://www.barks.jp/ Barks Global Music Explorer]|accessdate=2009-05-24}}</ref> and ''Dear Call Girl'' on July 11, 2007 through the same company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barks.jp/cdreview/?id=2000455298|title=Dear Call Girl|publisher=[http://www.barks.jp/ Barks Global Music Explorer]|accessdate=2009-05-24}}</ref> They also performed at the Erotic Rock Festival in [[Shibuya, Tokyo]] in May 2007 with several AV actresses in attendance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allabout.co.jp/entertainment/adultvideo/closeup/CU20070507A/|title=ＣＡＭＰＡＫＥＸライブレポ＆トークイベント開催！|publisher=[http://allabout.co.jp/ AllAbout]|last=Otsubo|first=Kemuta|date=May 21, 2007|accessdate=2009-05-24|language=Japanese}}</ref> The group was dissolved in June 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allabout.co.jp/entertainment/adultvideo/closeup/CU20070609A/|title=電撃発表！ＣＡＭＰＡＫＥＸ解散宣言|publisher=[http://allabout.co.jp/ AllAbout]|last=Otsubo|first=Kemuta|date=June 27, 2007|accessdate=2009-05-24|language=Japanese}}</ref>
